HEADWORD: Presuppose
<hw>Pre`sup*pose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Presupposed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Presupposing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pre-</ets> + <ets>suppose</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧supposer</ets>.]</ety> <def>To suppose beforehand; to
imply as antecedent; to take for granted; to assume; <as>as, creation
<ex>presupposes</ex> a creator</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each [kind of knowledge] <qex>presupposes</qex> many necessary
things learned in other sciences, and known beforehand.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presupposition</ent>⟦br⟧
